OL,3,GOPINIONCITV sale: what once would've
OL,4,Cbeen considered unthinkable now
OL,5,Cregarded as a rescue deal
OL,6,
OL,7,FMind you, I'm not so sure the
OL,8,Fannouncers need to add a "thank you".
OL,9,FIt reminds me too much of hard-up PBS
OL,10,Fstations in the USA begging for money.
OL,11,FPerhaps promos should be made instead?
OL,13,FBut the point stands. If broadcasting
OL,14,Fis a public service, broadcasters needs
OL,15,Fto have a relationship with the public.
OL,17,FIt might be the BBC's relationship with
OL,18,Flicence payers and the scrutiny which
OL,19,Fcomes with it.
OL,23,Uppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppppp
